author: National Geographic
description:
Not yet ready for spooky season to end? Join National Geographic and explore some of the most haunted locations around the world in this Atlas of Cursed Places MEGA episode. Featuring full episodes: 

The Curse of West Virginia
Sam arrives in West Virginia to study the curse of the Mothman, but things go awry once he uncovers a web of disasters and dirty politics. 

The Curse of the Bermuda Triangle
Sam dives deep to get to the bottom of the curse of the Bermuda Triangle, a stretch of ocean where people disappear without explanation. Or do they?  

The Curse of Atlantis
Sam investigates the utopian city, Atlantis, that Plato says was cursed by the gods and swallowed up into the sea 12,000 years ago. 

The Curse of Vlad the Impaler
Sam investigates the curse of Vlad Tepes, a 15th century eastern European ruler whose curse upon his Romanian homeland has lasted for six centuries.

description:
